         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The United Kingdom Ministry of Defence (The authority) is seeking to procure a hydrophobic coating to be applied to its fleet of Chinook helicopters. The authority intends to place a single source contract with PPG Industries (UK) Ltd (PPG) for the procurement of their Surface Seal® product with an approximate value of 285 000 GBP. This contract will be for the product application kits, technical advice and support for the initial embodiment, and will include an enabling contract for the supply of spares and tooling for a 1 year period.</P>
                     <P>It is considered that this contract can be placed using the negotiated procedure without prior publication pursuant to Article 32(2)(b)(ii) of Directive 2014/24/EU of the European Parliament and of the Council (Regulation 32(2)(b)(ii) of the public contract Regulations 2015) for urgent safety and technical reasons. An Urgent Statement of User Requirement (USUR), actioned by the Chinook Force Commander, endorsed by Joint Helicopter Command (JHC), has been received by the Chinook Delivery Team (ChDT), outlining the urgent need to embody Surface Seal® on the RAF Chinook fleet in order to mitigate the increased risk of Mid-Air Collision (MAC) and Controlled Flight Into Terrain (CFIT).</P>
                     <P>The authority’s requirement is to embody the hydrophobic windscreen coating on the Chinook fleet as soon as possible in view of the safety implications. The engineering and qualification activities required for introducing a modification of this type on to a military platform are expensive, complicated and take a considerable amount of time and effort to complete. Surface Seal® is the only such product which has been formally cleared for use on the UK Chinook fleet within the Release to Service (RTS). PPG is the OEM of Surface Seal® and their support and technical advice is required in addition to the embodiment kits. Although Surface Seal® has been cleared for use on the Chinook, the current approved embodiment method does not allow for embodiment on-wing. This greatly increases the time to fleet embody, and due to the urgent requirement, on-wing procedures need to be trialled and approved. The OEM is required to assist in this activity, as well as providing training to personnel who will be carrying out the embodiment.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
